plot: Ross finds a way to make Emma laugh - singing "Baby Got Back." Meanwhile, Phoebe meets Mike's parents, and Joey and Chandler find a video tape in Richard's apartment.

Joey has earned too much money to keep hiding it in his bathroom, so Monica suggests investing in real estate, such as Richard's apartment which is for sale; Chandler accompanies him, and they find a videotape marked "Monica". After some coaching from slick ideal daughter-in-law Rachel, Phoebe has her first dinner with boyfriend Mike's classy parents and some boring acquaintances, but despite a phony British accent she's too much herself not to shock and disgust, yet Mike sticks with her, and more. Ross is the first to get baby daughter Emma to really laugh, but Rachel is shocked to hear he did it by singing a rap song about big buttocks; nevertheless, she's more envious.—KGF Vissers

Ross gets Emma to laugh by singing "Baby Got Back". This enrages Rachel, but Rachel sings it herself after multiple failed attempts at getting her to laugh. Joey invests his salary into real estate, specifically Richard's apartment. Chandler joins them and is furious after watching a tape marked "Monica", but it is not what he thinks. Phoebe tries her best to impress Mike's rich parents and their friends. Her failed attempts at getting them to like her leads to Mike declaring his love for her.—gdubs-41348
